Center: Indian Compilation Group: BARC and others, India
title: Fission fragment angular momentum in the spontaneous fission of 244-Cm

x4freetext: Fission fragment angular momentum in the spontaneous
fission of 244-Cm

x4codes.hlp: Bhabha Atomic Research Centre (BARC), Trombay, Mumbai, India

x4freetext: An electrodeposited source of 99.43 atom % of 244-Cm
was prepared on a thin platinum planchet from an
isopropyl alcohol medium. The target was heated red
hot to fix the activity to the planchet.
The recoiling fission products from the
244-Cm target were collected on 0.0075 cm thick Lexan
(polycarbonate) catcher foils kept  at a distance 6
mm from the target in 2 pi geometry for 2 to 60 hours
depending upon the half lives of the nuclides of
interest. After the exposure the lexan foils were
removed, washed with very dilute nitric acid and
distilled water to remove any possible contamination of
244-Cm. They were then mounted on a Perspex plate and
counted at a fixed geometry and efficiency calibrated
120 c.c. HPGe detector.
The lexan foils were counted at a fixed
geometry on an energy and efficiency calibrated 120
c.c HPGe detector coupled to a 4096 channel analyzer
in live time mode. The resolution of the detector
system was 1.8 keV at 1332 keV of 60-Co. The dead
time was kept at less than 10% to avoid pile up effect.
From the photo peak areas of gamma rays of the
nuclides of interest, independent isomeric yield
ratios were calculated using usual decay growth
equation after correcting for the precursor
contribution.  The activities of 92-Sr was used as the
fission rate monitor.

x4code.headerHelp: Error in value of quantity, defined under ERR-ANALYS

x4freetext: The uncertainty on the independent
isomeric yield ratios includes the error due to
counting statistics, absolute abundance of the gamma
lines, detector efficiencies, the fission yields of the
precursor and the least square analysis.
The gamma lines and the nuclear spectroscopic data
of different nuclides were taken from:
E.Browne and R.B.Firestone, in Table of Radioactive
Isotopes, edited by V.S.Shirley (Wiley & Sons,NY,1986)
and
J.Blachot, Ch.Fiche, Ann.Phys. (Paris) 6, 3-218(1981).
fission fragment angular momenta (Jrms)
Compiled by Mr. Paresh Prajapati of The
M.S. University of Baroda and Dr. Sarbjit Singh of
Radiochemistry Divison of B.A.R.C, Mumbai.
Entry approved by Dr. H. Naik
